# gid

A CLI tool for switching between multiple GitHub accounts via SSH profiles.

## Install

```bash
go install .
```

Make sure `~/go/bin` is in your `$PATH`.

## Setup

```bash
gid setup
```

Walks you through configuring each profile — name, email, SSH key generation, and GitHub key registration.

Profiles are stored in `~/.gid/profiles.json`.

## Usage

```bash
# Switch to a profile
gid use tulay

# Show active profile
gid status

# Test SSH connection
gid test tulay
```

## Starship Integration

Add this to your `~/.config/starship.toml` to show the active profile in your prompt:

```toml
[custom.gid]
command = """grep -o '"active": *"[^"]*"' ~/.gid/profiles.json 2>/dev/null | cut -d'"' -f4"""
when = "test -f ~/.gid/profiles.json"
symbol = "🔑 "
format = "[$symbol($output)]($style) "
style = "bold purple"
shell = ["bash", "--noprofile", "--norc"]
```
